item.title: InsidiaX Skill Tab
item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

NetBeans is what I use although you could use Eclipse too. If you have a fast pc use NetBeans. Otherwise it would be best to use Eclipse. Then simply go to file open file and look for the java file that is throwing the error. Then in the IDE it will underline where the problem starts (where you need to add a bracket) or it will underline the bracket if you have too many. When downloading NetBeans you can just select the Java options if you are only going to use for your RSPS.
